existence disclosed through shifting narrative accounts by youth and their families as they grapple with psychiatric diagnosis, poverty, misogyny, and stigma in their trajectories through multiple forms of harm and sites of care. Csordas and Jenkins compellingly direct our attention to the conjunction of lived experience, institutional power, and the very possibility of having a life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aAdolescent psychiatryzNew Mexico. 0aAdolescent psychotherapyxResidential treatmentzNew Mexico. 0aPsychiatric hospital carezNew Mexico. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aadolescents hospitalized for psychiatric care.  acultural phenomenology of existence.  afamilial turmoil.  agripping.  agroundbreaking.  amental health care system.  amisogyny.  anew mexico.  apersonal anguish and structural violence.  apoverty.  apsychiatric diagnosis.  apsychic distress.  astigma.  atreatment under regime of managed care.1 aCsordas, Thomas J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520975019zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520975019423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520975019.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC P